Extract Bayes Factors from BayesFactor model object.

Source: R/helpers_bf_tests.R
bf_extractor.Rd

Extract Bayes Factors from BayesFactor model object.

bf_extractor(bf.object, ...)

Arguments

bf.object

An object from BayesFactor package.
...

Currently ignored.

Examples

# getting only Bayes Factors
statsExpressions::bf_extractor(
  BayesFactor::anovaBF(
    formula = Sepal.Length ~ Species,
    data = iris,
    progress = FALSE
  )
)
#> # A tibble: 1 x 7
#>      bf10        error     bf01 log_e_bf10 log_e_bf01 log_10_bf10 log_10_bf01
#>     <dbl>        <dbl>    <dbl>      <dbl>      <dbl>       <dbl>       <dbl>
#> 1 1.43e28 0.0000000651 7.02e-29       64.8      -64.8        28.2       -28.2
